# farm_soil robot credentials.
#
# Copy to ttn.env (same directory) and fill in the real values. ttn.env is
# gitignored — never commit it. run.sh sources this file into the process
# environment before launching the robot.
#
# ─── TTN bearer token (moisture KB) ──────────────────────────────────
# A TTN v3 application API key, format NNSXS.<id>.<secret>. ttn_client
# passes it via a transient `curl -K` config file, never argv. If ever
# committed in plaintext, rotate it at TTN — a git history rewrite does not
# un-expose it.
TTN_BEARER_TOKEN=NNSXS.xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx.xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# ─── CIMIS appKey (cimis_station + cimis_spatial KBs) ────────────────
# An et.water.ca.gov developer key, UUID format. The CIMIS API requires it
# as a URL query parameter — so the URL itself carries the secret.
# cimis_client writes the whole URL into a transient `curl -K` config file
# (never argv), keeping the appKey out of `ps`. Like the TTN token: if
# ever committed in plaintext, rotate it at et.water.ca.gov.
CIMIS_APP_KEY=00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
